Eclat Algorithm¶

Equivalence Class Algorithm¶

So in eclat we just go through the depth first search method to get the frequent item sets¶

An advantage in using this type of algorithm is that is uses less memory when compared to the Apriori as in most of the cases we would have the number of transactions to be more than the count of items¶

hence Eclat is faster to compute than the Apriori¶

hrere we take the item sets , and construct a prefix tree as shown for each item in lexicographic order and generate the frequent item set¶

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ecPEXnZQok0

FP - Growth Algorithm¶

Frequent Pattern growth Algorithm¶

FP growth algorithm is considered to be fast as than Ecat , because here we first sort the items in the decreasing order of their support¶

We then start to to grow the FP tree in depth wise manner , sorting the items will now reduce the number of nodes in our tree¶

https://www.slideshare.net/wanaezwani/apriori-and-eclat-algorithm-in-association-rule-mining

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VB8KWm8MXss
